body:
I would be great if Verilator would fuse all files it read into a single file. This would make it easier to produce test cases for issues.

Example:

Let's say that Verilator is called with `verilator +incdir+<some-dir> <some-dir>/some_package.sv <some-other-dir>/some_module.sv`:

```
// file: some_package.sv
package some_package;
  `include "some_class.svh"
  `include "some_other_class.svh"
endpackage
```

```
// file: some_class.svh
class some_class;
endclass
```

```
// file: some_other_class.svh
class some_other_class;
endclass
```

```
// file: some_module.sv
module some_module;
  import some_package::*;
endmodule
```

To make it easy to create a test case out of this, Verilator could produce a `test.sv` containing everything from the files listed above:

```
// file: test.sv
package some_package;

class some_class;
endclass

class some_other_class;
endclass

endpackage

module some_module;
  import some_package::*;
endmodule
```

The user could then just attach the test.sv, instead of having to create an archive out of their code.
